    <stitle>Body Builder Electrical Data Book - SINGLE REDUCTION AXLES: SPICER S100-S, S105-S, S135-S, S150-S -
        DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="5">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401710">Figure 10</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401710" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401710" filename="../figg14/G1401710.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Differential Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match mark differential case halves with punch or chisel for correct alignment in
                    reassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401711">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401711" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401711" filename="../figg14/G1401711.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Match Mark Differential Case Halves With Punch or Chisel</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential case bolts and lift off differential case half.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thrust washer and differential side gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out cross shaft, pinion mates, and thrust washers.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove second differential side gear and thrust washer.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If differential side bearings are to be replaced, remove old bearings using a suitable
                    puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401712">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401712" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401712" filename="../figg14/G1401712.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Remove Old Bearings Using a Suitable Puller</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inspect all parts, including the machined surfaces of the case half.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>If any gears are to be replaced, they must be replaced in sets. Inspect thrust washers for scoring and
                excessive wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When it is necessary to remove ring gear from the differential case, carefully center
                    punch each rivet head. Using a 9/16 inch drill bit, drill through rivet heads to depth shown. Next,
                    use a rounded type punch to drive out remaining portion of the rivet (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401713">Figure 13</hotlnk>
                    and
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401714">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1401713" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401713" filename="../figg14/G1401713.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Drive Out Remaining Portion of Rivet (Correct Procedure)</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1401714" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1401714" filename="../figg14/G1401714.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="192px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Drive Out Remaining Portion of Rivet (Incorrect Procedure)</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Always use a soft hammer or H.D. plastic head hammer to strike punch.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use a chisel to remove rivet heads, damage to differential case may result.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
